Some clarifications: When I say "paper cutouts", I mean simple colored shapes like circles and triangles, assembled one on op of another. This seems like something a language model could manage reasonably well. Let's take a step back and work on a REQUIREMENTS.md please. We want a system that can handle all the concerns in the concept, while providing the other qualities we've discussed. We should use purpose-oriented language for now (for example, "paper cutouts" will be a later design detail; the real requirement is that we present our artwork in a manner that a language model can generate and animate). Let's also downscope to web previews: We should just have an engine that can efficiently read these files and display them in-browser. That's something we can later orchestrate to render things at higher resolutions. (Maybe mention that in a "deferred requirements" section or something.)

