Great work! One note is that "Voice Integration (TTS)" seems a bit over-specified; we could still produce episodes by hiring voice actors for those parts, for example. The system should generate audio performances for dialog lines; we'll also need distinct voices per-character. I think there's also a series/episode/scene hierarchy that we haven't quite captured here; that is, I think we need some requirements around scenes (e.g. we can control locations of characters, timing of animations and dialog within scenes) and perhaps some series/episode sub-requirements for those relationships. Also, while the FR-01 style is handy, it's a bit dry for us; maybe just use emoji shortcodes or something for now. Could you produce another draft?

ğŸª„âœ¨ write(project:aniheim,file:REQUIREMENTS.md) {
File written.
} writeâš¡ï¸

---

Excellent work. Now, I'd like a SPECIFICATION.md which evolves this forward just a little. We don't want to get into design or implementation details yet (e.g. APIs or lines of code), but we want everything well-defined with clear traces to requirements. For example, we might commit to character representation being handled in a library of JS modules in the SPECIFICATION, but we don't need to design a character API or describe the directory structure which might hold characters. Feel free to get a little creative and inventive, but remember that our goal is to get highly-entertaining, engaging animation out of language models. This is a good opportunity to think through things like the paper cut-out approach, and figure out which ones really suit our resources. Oh, and again, this is a first cut at a big project, so let's look for opportunities to meet our requirements with minimal scope and simple solutins. Thank you!

