Now for the fun part: Please draft a `DESIGN.md` which covers all of the major interfaces of the system. We want enough inforrmation here to build and use the system; a full definition of interfaces needed to meet the specification. Include command-line invocation (how will we render episode files?). Prefer microformats; e.g. consider interspersing emoji in dialog ğŸ˜® to control character expressions ğŸ˜€, for example. Maybe we can do that for poses as well? ğŸ¤· Similarly, MML is a cute choice for a music, but ABC Notation might also work. We ultimately want something that (a) an LLM can easily produce using a semantic understanding of music theory and (b) we can easily render to `.mp3` or similar using mostly off-the-shelf tools. We'd like to apply the same mentality to animation formats, scene sequencing, etc... Oh, finally, let's try to have one episode per file for now (maybe with hyperlinks to music and character files to manage size) with the important thing being that having one file containing the full story and all dialog will be helpful for narrative clarity (both in reviewing episodes before rendering to HTML, and in generating them). We're free to bring LLMs in-the-loop, too, so a `/music(file:mp3) { A melodic piano piece, serene and suitable for a}` directive is viable (it could call out to an LLM to MML or ABC or similar, then we can render that to `.mp3` via MIDI and some SoundFonts). Perhaps parameterizing it like `/music(sheet:some/abc/file,audio:some/file.mp3) { ... }` can be used to canonicalize file locations (so we skip re-rendering if files exist, and trigger regeneration by deleting files).

Sorry, that's a lot I'm dumping out, but please take a shot at a `DESIGN.md`. Really appreciating your work!

